abstract: A New York Times/Siena College survey in six key states also showed voters want a candidate who can work with Republicans.
snippet: A New York Times/Siena College survey in six key states also showed voters want a candidate who can work with Republicans.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats in the country’s most pivotal general election battlegrounds prefer a moderate presidential nominee who would seek common ground with Republicans rather than pursue an ambitious, progressive agenda, according to a New York Times/Siena College poll of primary voters across six states.

abstract: Mr. Sanders released a plan on Thursday that vowed to create a “swift, fair pathway to citizenship” for undocumented immigrants.
snippet: Mr. Sanders released a plan on Thursday that vowed to create a “swift, fair pathway to citizenship” for undocumented immigrants.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders on Thursday called for ending virtually all of the Trump administration’s immigration policies and creating a “swift, fair pathway to citizenship” for undocumented immigrants, including by allowing people who have been in the United States illegally for five years to stay without the risk of deportation.

abstract: As he steps up his efforts in Iowa, Mr. Sanders is using a traditional media platform to try to bring new voters into the political system to support him.
snippet: As he steps up his efforts in Iowa, Mr. Sanders is using a traditional media platform to try to bring new voters into the political system to support him.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders’s campaign plans to spend more than $30 million on TV advertising alone in the first four presidential nominating states and California, according to several people familiar with the strategy, a financial show of force that also suggests he needs to reach outside the traditional sphere of Democratic primary voters and caucusgoers for support.

abstract: Let’s put an end to this racist trope.
snippet: Let’s put an end to this racist trope.
lead_paragraph: Reducing Pete Buttigieg’s struggle to attract black support solely to black homophobia is not only erroneous, it is a disgusting, racist trope, secretly nursed and insidiously whispered by white liberals with contempt for the very black people they court and need.

abstract: “Ok billionaire” is a better rallying cry than “ok boomer.”
snippet: “Ok billionaire” is a better rallying cry than “ok boomer.”
lead_paragraph: Generations are pretty bogus. The labels we use to casually slice up society — boomer, millennial, Gen X, Gen Z — are a nearly useless way of thinking about politics, culture or business in America. The very idea that tens of millions of people across different classes and races and geographies might hold similar views on a range of subjects just because they happened to be born during the same 20-year span of American history — the whole thing sounds a bit too much like astrology, doesn’t it?

headline_main: Instead of a Generational Culture War, Let’s Fight the Rich

abstract: A single-payer system can lower prices by setting them. But lots of countries regulate prices and have private insurance, too.
snippet: A single-payer system can lower prices by setting them. But lots of countries regulate prices and have private insurance, too.
lead_paragraph: One way Elizabeth Warren wants to control health care spending in the United States is simple in principle: Pay doctors and hospitals significantly less.

headline_main: Warren Has Her Plan. Buttigieg Suggests Another Way to Cut Health Prices.
headline_print_headline: Warren’s Plan Targets Insurers. Buttigieg Aims at Hospitals.

abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. unfurled sharply personal new lines of attack against Senator Elizabeth Warren on Tuesday, questioning her contributions to the Democratic Party and seeking to cast her as an elitist who believes people lack courage or wisdom unless they agree with her.

abstract: President Trump’s decision to quit the Paris climate accord met with harsh words from the Democratic presidential candidates.
snippet: President Trump’s decision to quit the Paris climate accord met with harsh words from the Democratic presidential candidates.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s decision on Monday to begin the formal process of withdrawing from the Paris climate agreement prompted outrage from the Democratic presidential candidates, who may try to use the existential threat of climate change to motivate voters.
